com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium

Interface Cookie


  • public interface Cookie
    Represents an HTTP cookie.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      long getCreationTime()
      Returns cookie creation time in microseconds since Windows epoch.
      java.lang.String getDomain()
      Returns the domain name set for this cookie.
      long getExpirationTime()
      Returns cookie expiration time in microseconds since Windows epoch.
      java.lang.String getName()
      Returns the name of the cookie.
      java.lang.String getPath()
      Returns the path on the server to which the browser returns this cookie.
      long getUnixCreationTime()
      Returns cookie creation time in seconds since UNIX epoch.
      long getUnixExpirationTime()
      Returns cookie expiration time in seconds since UNIX epoch.
      java.lang.String getValue()
      Returns the value of the cookie.
      boolean isHTTPOnly()
      Returns true if this cookie contains the HttpOnly attribute.
      boolean isSecure()
      Returns true if sending this cookie should be restricted to a secure protocol, or false if the it can be sent using any protocol.
      boolean isSession()
      Returns true if this cookie is a session cookie without expiration time and false if this cookie is a persistent cookie that has expiration time.

    • Method Detail

      • getName

        java.lang.String getName()
        Returns the name of the cookie.
        Returns:
        a String specifying the cookie's name.

      • getValue

        java.lang.String getValue()
        Returns the value of the cookie.
        Returns:
        a String containing the cookie's present value.

      • getDomain

        java.lang.String getDomain()
        Returns the domain name set for this cookie.
        Returns:
        a String containing the domain name.

      • getPath

        java.lang.String getPath()
        Returns the path on the server to which the browser returns this cookie. The cookie is visible to all subpaths on the server.
        Returns:
        a String specifying a path that contains a servlet name, for example, /catalog.

      • getCreationTime

        long getCreationTime()
        Returns cookie creation time in microseconds since Windows epoch. The returned value equals the number of microseconds since January 1, 1601.
        Returns:
        the creation time in microseconds.

      • getUnixCreationTime

        long getUnixCreationTime()
        Returns cookie creation time in seconds since UNIX epoch. The returned value equals the number of seconds since January 1, 1970.
        Returns:
        the creation time in seconds.
        Since:
        6.12

      • getExpirationTime

        long getExpirationTime()
        Returns cookie expiration time in microseconds since Windows epoch. The returned value equals the number of microseconds since January 1, 1601.
        Returns:
        the expiration time in microseconds.

      • getUnixExpirationTime

        long getUnixExpirationTime()
        Returns cookie expiration time in seconds since UNIX epoch. The returned value equals the number of seconds since January 1, 1970.
        Returns:
        the creation time in seconds.
        Since:
        6.12

      • isSecure

        boolean isSecure()
        Returns true if sending this cookie should be restricted to a secure protocol, or false if the it can be sent using any protocol.
        Returns:
        false if the cookie can be sent over any standard protocol; otherwise, true.

      • isHTTPOnly

        boolean isHTTPOnly()
        Returns true if this cookie contains the HttpOnly attribute. This means that the cookie should not be accessible to scripting engines, like javascript.
        Returns:
        true if this cookie should be considered http only.

      • isSession

        boolean isSession()
        Returns true if this cookie is a session cookie without expiration time and false if this cookie is a persistent cookie that has expiration time.
